Step 1 — Modify IAM Role on EC2:
      Go to AWS Console → EC2 → Instances
      Select your running EC2 Instance
      Click Actions → Security → Modify IAM Role
Step 2 — Attach the Role:
      In the IAM Role dropdown, select: DemoForEC2
      Click "Update IAM Role" to save
Step 3 — Verify via EC2 Instance Terminal:
      Connect to your EC2 Instance via SSH or EC2 Instance Connect
      Run the following AWS CLI command: aws iam list-users
      If the role is attached correctly, it will return the list of IAM users ✅
Step 4 — Result:
      The DemoForEC2 Role is now attached to the EC2 Instance, 
      which allows the EC2 instance to make AWS API calls on your behalf.
